Offer Initiation by Users:

SELECT
  app_id,
  COUNT(DISTINCT offer_id) AS total_offers_initiated
FROM
  user_offer_data
GROUP BY
  app_id;

This query counts the number of distinct offers initiated by users for each app. It provides insights into the engagement level of users with the offers in each app.


Offer Completion by Users:

SELECT
  app_id,
  COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS total_users_completed_offers,
  COUNT(DISTINCT offer_id) AS total_offers_completed
FROM
  user_offer_completion_data
GROUP BY
  app_id;

This query counts the number of distinct users and offers completed for each app. It helps understand the user engagement and the effectiveness of offers in driving completion.


Rewards Earned by Users:

SELECT
  app_id,
  COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS total_users_earning_rewards,
  SUM(total_payout_in_paise) / 100 AS total_payout,
  SUM(total_revenue_in_paise) / 100 AS total_revenue
FROM
  user_offer_completion_data uc
JOIN
  rewards_details r ON uc.reward_id = r.reward_id
GROUP BY
  app_id;

This query calculates the number of users earning rewards, total payout, and total revenue generated by each app. It provides insights into the effectiveness of the reward system in driving user engagement.



Revenue Generated:

SELECT
  app_id,
  SUM(total_revenue_in_paise) / 100 AS total_revenue
FROM
  rewards_details
GROUP BY
  app_id;

This query calculates the total revenue generated by each app based on the rewards offered. It helps determine the financial performance of each app.
